        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 24 at 9:30PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 929 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Lake Mcclellan, or 17 miles north of Clarendon, moving southwest at 5
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lake Mcclellan.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1100 PM CDT for
the Panhandle of Texas.</instruction>
